    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="1855"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1855">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 033 1100 K77/166.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Minister of Venezuela</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Venezuela</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 18, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to offer to your
                    excellency my congratulations on the sentiments of American fraternity which
                    inspired your recent visit to some of the countries on our continent and
                    especially on the very good impression created in Venezuela by your excellency’s
                    visit.</p>
                <p>The pleasant remembrance of that visit will ever be treasured in my country as a
                    new bond of friendship that must strengthen more and more the cordial relations
                    existing between the Venezuelan nation and the great Republic of the United
                    States.</p>
                <p>I avail myself [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">F. Ezequiel Rojas.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
